The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 In tandem

 Bharata Natyam virtuosos V.P. Dhananjayan and Shanta Dhananjayan have accomplished much in spreading Indian cultural heritage all over the world. In recognition of their efforts, Spandan and Nrityalok host an evening of Bharata Natyam to honour and felicitate one of the finest pairs of exponents of this classical dance form. Featuring a Bharata Natyam duet by Sutapa Awon Pradhan (picture along) and Umesh Bheemanna Madesh, who are both students of the Dhananjayans, Jugal Bandi stays true to their gurus? essence of purity in performance, devotion and dedication to dance. Choreographed by none other than the Dhananjayans themselves, the recital displays a perfect balance between traditionalism and contemporary freshness, a hallmark of their distinctive style of performance.

 Event: Bharata Natyam duet by Sutapa Awon Pradhan and Umesh Bheemanna Madesh

 When: Today at 6.30 pm

 Where: Gyan Manch




